info.name: Cuneate fasciculus
info.description: The cuneate fasciculus is the lateral portion of the dorsal or posterior column rostral to T6. It includes large, uncrossed, primary afferent fibers carrying tactile, vibratory and proprioceptive input from the upper extremity and the body above approximately T6; most of these fibers will terminate in the cuneate and lateral cuneate nuclei in the medulla.
